about.summary: Supports the analysis of Oceanographic data, including 'ADCP' measurements, measurements made with 'argo' floats, 'CTD' measurements, sectional data, sea-level time series, coastline and topographic data, etc. Provides specialized functions for calculating seawater properties such as potential temperature in either the 'UNESCO' or 'TEOS-10' equation of state. Produces graphical displays that conform to the conventions of the Oceanographic literature.

name: r-oce
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1-1" %}

{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-oce
  version: {{ version.replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: oce_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - http://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/oce_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - http://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/Archive/oce/oce_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2ce8f8d3adb3da5c8a09fda060e1ff79cad0f0f6f918f8fe64f51a6cd6b58e43

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  script: R CMD INSTALL --build .
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}      # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('fortran') }}  # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_fortran') }}        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp
    - r-gsw
    - r-testthat
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp
    - r-gsw
    - r-testthat

test:
  commands:
    - R -e "library('oce')"  # [not win]
    - R -e \"library('oce')\"  # [win]

about:
  home: http://dankelley.github.com/oce/
  license: GPL-3.0
  summary: "Supports the analysis of Oceanographic data, including 'ADCP' measurements,
    measurements made with 'argo' floats, 'CTD' measurements, sectional data,
    sea-level time series, coastline and topographic data, etc. Provides specialized
    functions for calculating seawater properties such as potential temperature
    in either the 'UNESCO' or 'TEOS-10' equation of state. Produces graphical
    displays that conform to the conventions of the Oceanographic literature."

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ocefpaf
